# CODING STANDARDS

> Unified rules for clean, readable, and maintainable code.

---

## LIMITS

| Metric | Limit | When exceeded |
|--------|-------|---------------|
| Lines per function | ≤ 50 | Split into sub-functions |
| Lines per file | ≤ 300 | Split into modules |
| Function parameters | ≤ 4 | Use object parameter |
| Nesting levels | ≤ 3 | Early returns |
| Characters per line | ≤ 100 | Line break |

---

## NAMING

### Function verbs
| Action | Prefix | Example |
|--------|--------|---------|
| Get | get | `getUser`, `getProducts` |
| Set | set | `setStatus`, `setConfig` |
| Create | create | `createOrder`, `createUser` |
| Update | update | `updateProfile` |
| Delete | delete/remove | `deleteUser`, `removeItem` |
| Check | is/has/can | `isValid`, `hasAccess` |
| Transform | to/from/parse | `toJSON`, `fromDTO` |
| Handle | handle/process | `handleSubmit`, `processPayment` |
| Validate | validate | `validateEmail` |

---

## COMMENTS

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — explain WHY
// Using setTimeout instead of requestAnimationFrame
// due to Safari modal animation bug
setTimeout(() => closeModal(), 0);

// ✅ GOOD — warning
// IMPORTANT: order matters. Validate first, then save
await validateOrder(order);
await saveOrder(order);

// ❌ BAD — obvious code
// Increment counter by 1
counter++;
```

### JSDoc for public functions

```typescript
/**
 * Calculate order total including discounts and shipping.
 *
 * @param items - Order items
 * @param discount - Discount percentage (0-100)
 * @param shippingCost - Shipping cost
 * @returns Total order amount
 */
function calculateOrderTotal(
  items: OrderItem[],
  discount: number,
  shippingCost: number
): number {
  const subtotal = items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price * item.quantity, 0);
  const discountAmount = subtotal * (discount / 100);
  return subtotal - discountAmount + shippingCost;
}
```

---

## FUNCTIONS

- Prefer pure functions (no side effects)
- One function — one responsibility
- Use default parameters
- Use destructuring
- Use optional chaining & nullish coalescing (`??` not `||`)
- Use template literals
- Use array methods (filter, map, reduce) over loops

---

## ANTI-PATTERNS

- ❌ Magic numbers/strings → use named constants
- ❌ Mutation of arguments → return new objects
- ❌ Nested ternary operators → use functions
- ❌ Double negation (`!isNotValid`) → use positive conditions

